I do not know if the man behind Shintou would call me friend or not...but i do hope he would respect my opinions and the way i play my RP as i do his <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uaeonii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aeonii</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://aeonii.freeservers.com/images/colors.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/15/02 5:07:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=229.topic&index=20>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Powerlevelling &amp; Twinking - Why do we care?</span><hr size=1> /sigh...  I tell myself not to post these things, but here I go again.  <br>
<br>
What is a casual RPer?  I am a casual RPer.<br>
<br>
I left my other servers because, I too, was tired of doods, phat lewt, and all that other stuff.  Yeah, I picked up &quot;woot&quot; from those other servers and I still keep it with me.  But I also picked up hooray, and yippie, too.  But I detest RoXor, and l33t and all that other stuff.  I can't even decipher half of it.<br>
<br>
When I was on other servers, I was flat out told that people would not want to group with me because &quot;Luminas showers a dreaded evil %t with the righteous glow of Smite!&quot; or because, &quot;You know you're speaking elvish, right?&quot;  Uh, yeah.  I'm an elf.  Or people making fun of my rhyming Bard.  That was her thing.  That was how I set her apart.  But, alas.  She was shunned.  But Luminas and Veralyn both zoned, and were omw (half the time, the other half - on my way), and oom, and camped for the night.  <br>
<br>
So I came to FV.  I created a background story for myself after being on a few days and getting the feel for the server.  You can read it if GuildMagic is working today.  And I still zone, am omw (or on my way, depending on what my fingers say, not my mind), and am oom.<br>
<br>
When I first came here and tried to &quot;wander through the magical curtain, &quot;Provide healing for %t by the Power of Tunare,&quot; and be &quot;out of the magical force that sustains my etheral energies,&quot; I was also shunned.<br>
<br>
  ~*~On this server.~*~ <br>
<br>
I even had to walk away from a dark elf who almost violently berated for my attempts at rp-ing by telling me repeatedly that &quot;'Drow' was copyrighted by AD&amp;D, ooc.&quot;  That was so not RPing.<br>
<br>
What's a gal to do?<br>
<br>
But, within my guildchat, I am oom.  I am zoning.  I am omw (or on my way).  When I meet you, I am pleased to make your acquiantance.  I will march forward, if you like, to right the wrongs of the gnolls inhabiting the lands.  Or I /gasp if you happen to be oppositely aligned from me.  Or if you set the tone for it, I will go on a raid with you.  But if you once tell me &quot;WTF!  D33d I RoXor with my PH4+ lewtz&quot; I think that we need to part ways.<br>
<br>
What is a Casual RPer?  I am a Casual RPer.  Don't hate me for it.  Don't dislike me for it.  Just let me be, as much as I will accomodate your 100% emmersion in RP and try not to break your illusion that you strive for everytime you click Enter Norrath.  (I know the above comments aren't directed at me specifically, I'm saying &quot;you&quot; and &quot;your&quot; generally.)  I **totally** respect it, and wish that I were better at it.  People get impatient with my lollygagging while I try to do that stuff (RP), so I have to speed it up a little with zone and omw, and cut some, well, a lot of my story line out.<br>
<br>
I always try to be helpful and friendly to those around me.  I even try to give the &quot;evil&quot; races the benefit of the doubt, until they show me that they are truly dedicated to their evil gods.  Then,  /gasp.<br>
<br>
I will never give up FV as my server of choice.  There is no Casual RP Preferred server.  No in-between places for the likes of me.<br>
<br>
C'mon people now, smile on your brother (or sister)<br>
Try to love one another right now.<br>
