<p align="center"><font size="1" color="#E1B500">Jyleel</font></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukimayasilverbark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kimaya Silverbark</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.alienexplorer.com/clipart/images5/wolf.pawprint2.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/15/02 6:54:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=229.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/bellsouthpwp/Groups/15/15568/pages/34736/Kimaya-60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_bigsmile.gif" align=absmiddle>  A Summary</span><hr size=1> Not that this thread is &quot;over&quot; by any stretch, but I've been impressed again by what's been posted here and I wanted to say so.  Also, it looks to me like there's a whole lot of common ground that's surfaced, so I thought I'd sum up the two main topics and -- you guessed it -- my take!<br>
<br>
Topic 1 (most common) - People have varying tolerances for differences in how people RP (or choose not to) in FV.  Some people like to gripe about it, some people like to get bossy, some people just live and let live.<br>
<br>
My opinion: No one is required to like anything I or anyone else does.  Hey, no one even has to CARE!  If something really grits on your nerves and you seriously need to vent about it, that's what the Soapbox is here for.  Of course, there can be a can of worms as others take advantage of their own right to disagree.  But so long as folks refrain from getting profane, demanding or insulting, I figure it's all good.<br>
<br>
My request: Please keep those rants out of game, except in /tells to people you know and don't mind.  As I've said before, even d00dz don't break my RP environment quite so quickly as someone griping about how someone RP's.  Also, please don't expect anyone to play the way you'd like any more than you'd play the way they like.<br>
<br>
Topic 2 (Championed by Shintou) - Non-RP has keel-hauled RPers on the other servers.  We don't want that to happen here.<br>
<br>
My opinion: As I’ve said, I understand this fear.  I’ve seen things go south in other environments, and I don’t want it to happen here, either. However, I don’t think hostility towards those we don’t consider RPers is the way to prevent that -- I’ve already posted details on that one.  But as folks keep saying that RPing frequently elicits RPing in return, I personally suspect the best we can do is to keep actively fostering that sense of community.  Hopefully, it will bear out.<br>
<br>
My request: Please give this server, and the players in it, the chance to succeed or fail before passing judgement.  As for those whose play-style is so very different from your own, please allow yourself to ignore them and focus on the RP you do enjoy.  <br>
<br>
I’ve had a really hard time with this one myself on a couple different points, but I’ve come to a conclusion: none of my “solutions” would actually do a darn thing to resolve what I see wrong in the game.  In fact, judgmental hostility actively hurts the environment only for people who care about the RP environment in the first place – RPers.  So I’ve moved to “live and let live” and have been much more able to focus on those who do respond to RP.<br>
<br>
Topic 3 (I’m making this one up) – Twinking is as IC for FV as it is relevant to RL.<br>
<br>
Why: I have a friend who’s dating a rich guy.  He takes her places neither of us could ever afford, and does so every weekend.  She gets really nice things.  I’ll admit to rolling my eyes at 16-yr-old twinks in BMWs, but I’ll also admit that I wish her friend would buy ME a car.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
My request: Get him to buy me a car!  Seriously though, I am happy for her.  My talk with her today is making me re-think the whole twinking thing in EQ, so I thought I’d share.<br>
 <p>---<BR>
Kimaya Silverbark<BR>
